From: Freaky <Freaky@UNItopia.rus.uni-stuttgart.de>
Short: foreach() and reserved words
Type: Bug
State: Done - fixed in 3.2.8-dev.176

Hi,

foreach hat wohl Probleme mit reserved words:

mixed *a;
a = ({ 1,2,3,4 });
foreach(int command: a)
    printf("Command:%O\n",command);

liefert immer 0 ;)

Command:0
Command:0
Command:0
Command:0

Analysis:
When the shadowing if the global identifier is detected, the compiler
used the ident* of the global to retrieve the number of the local -
which of course resulted in random memory accesses.
